121 the one who is placed on her left
122 is the father for whose bold taste
123 the human race tastes so much bitterness;

133 Opposite Peter you see Anne seated,
134 so content to gaze at her daughter,
135 that she does not move her eyes to sing hosanna;

139 But because the time flees that makes you drowsy,
140 here we will make a stop, like a good tailor
